\frac{x-a}{b}-\frac{x+c}{d}=0
x=\frac{ad+bc}{d-b}
 \frac{x}{b} - \frac{a}{b} -\frac{x}{d}-\frac{c}{d} =0
\frac{x}{b}-\frac{x}{d} = \frac{a}{b}+\frac{c}{d}
\Longrightarrow x \Bigl(\frac{d-b}{bd}\Bigr) = \frac{ad+bc}{bd}
bd
\frac{x-a}{b}-\frac{x+c}{d}=0
bd\left(\frac{x-a}{b}-\frac{x+c}{d}\right)=0.
bd\left(\frac{x-a}{b}-\frac{x+c}{d}\right)=d(x-a)-b(x+c).
d(x-a)-b(x+c)=0.
(d-b)x-ad-bc=0,\quad\text{or equivalently}\quad (d-b)x=ad+bc.
d \ne b
x=\frac{ad+bc}{d-b}.
d=b
(0)x=ad+bc.
d=b
(0)x=b(a+c)
c=-a
